org.chronos.chronodb.internal.api.cache

Interface CacheGetResult<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of the actual result data contained in this cache get result. Used for the return type of getValue().
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CacheGetResultImpl

    public interface CacheGetResult<T>
    A CacheGetResult represents the result of calling ChronoDBCache.get(String, long, org.chronos.chronodb.api.key.QualifiedKey).

    An instance of this class may either represent a cache hit, in which case isHit() returns true and getValue() delivers the actual result data, or it may represent a cache miss , in which case isHit() returns false and getValue() will always throw a CacheGetResultNotPresentException.

    • Method Detail

      • miss

        static <T> CacheGetResult<T> miss()
        Returns the singleton CacheGetResult instance representing a cache miss.

        Calling isHit() on the returned instance will always return false. Calling getValue() on the returned instance will always throw a CacheGetResultNotPresentException.

        Type Parameters:
        T - The data type of the value returned by getValue(). In this case, this parameter is never used, as getValue() always throws a CacheGetResultNotPresentException.
        Returns:
        The singleton instance representing a cache miss. Never null.

      • hit

        static <T> CacheGetResult<T> hit(T value)
        Creates a new CacheGetResult instance representing a cache hit.

        An instance created by this method will never throw a CacheGetResultNotPresentException on getValue().

        Type Parameters:
        T - The data type of the value returned by getValue().
        Parameters:
        value - The result value to return in getValue() in the new instance.
        Returns:
        The newly created cache get result instance. Never null.

      • isHit

        boolean isHit()
        Checks if this cache result represents a "cache hit".

        If this method returns true, then getValue() returns the actual result value. If this method returns false, then getValue() will always throw a CacheGetResultNotPresentException.

        Returns:
        true if this result represents a cache hit, or false if it represents a cache miss.
        See Also:
        isMiss()

      • getValue

        T getValue()
    throws CacheGetResultNotPresentException
        Returns the value associated with this cache query result.

        If isHit() returns true, then this method will return the actual result value. If isHit() returns false, this method will always throw a CacheGetResultNotPresentException.

        Returns:
        The actual query result.
        Throws:
        CacheGetResultNotPresentException - Thrown if this instance represents a cache miss (this.isHit() returns false) and this.getValue() is called.

      • isMiss

        default boolean isMiss()
        Checks if this cache result represents a "cache miss".

        If this method returns true, then getValue() will always throw a CacheGetResultNotPresentException. If this method returns false, then getValue() will return the actual result data.

        Returns:
        true if this result represents a cache miss, or false if it represents a cache hit.
        See Also:
        isHit()
